	   <tr><td colspan=2>I did this quest last night and it seems that everyone seems to say "THIS IS HOW IT IS...I DID IT AND IT GOES THE SAME WAY FOR EVERYONE EVERY TIME."&nbsp;&nbsp;I am here to say this is how it went for me when I did the quest.  <br><br>I got the Harness of Control from Vores, and went near the river to bring up track to see if the Broodmother was up.  As it happened, she was, however, some UBER guild was doing the 10th ring quest and shouted to the zone that anyone who did not want to get slammed by 200+ giants to get out of the zone.  I figured why chance it...and lose my leggins, Im out of here.  I came back after the quest was confirmed to be over and all the normal mobs in the zone re-popped (including the Broodmother).  I refreshed SoW, Invised up, medded to full, and headed into the first cavern to the left which twisted around a bit.  I got behind the Broodmother and turned the harness into her.  it gave some message like "her neck snapps and she begins heading out of the cave".  I re-invised up and followed running along side and near her. (BTW I highly reccomend having someone do this quest with you, stand near the Frost giant camp to ensure that no one steals, or attacks Fergul before the Broodmother gets there)  I took a chance and decided to /shout to the zone that I was doing a Quest and to please leave both the Broodmother and the two giants alone until I was finished.  It took about 2 to 3 minuites for the Broodmother to get to the camp.  She first goes up to the entrance to the camp as if she was going in, then circles back and attacks Grakkal.  At this point Fergul despawned.  I turned tward the zone, and he popped running away from me.  Due to seeing many posts here saying that get Fergul away from the action before aggroing I waited a bit before actually attempting to snare.  Snare held immediately (54 Druid) and then I kited him to the zone wall to avoid any adds.  I rooted, and casted Winged Death and meditated.  Im assuming after the Broodmother killed Grakkal, she made her way over to Fergul because I saw her come up and stop by his side.  I then knew that the "pet" stories are true.  I was almost afraid to reaply Winged Death on Fergul for fear that the BM would come up and attack (like normal pets do).  I casted, and she remained next to him.  I continued rooting and Dotting until he was half dead, and then I ended up not getting root fast enough and he came within Melee range.  This is where all hell broke loose, the instant i was in Fergul's range, the BM attacked and assisted Fergul.  I gained some distance between the two NPC's and  re-rooted Fergul.  The broodmother stopped by him and again acted like an unaggro pet.  Eventually I killed Fergul, the Broodmother then Depopped, and looted my leggings.  After this ordeal, I petitioned a GM and mentioned what had happened, he said to please do /bug and report my findings, and that he was happy to see  that I was able to get my leggins even with the reported trouble I had.  I /bug and hopefully all will see the patch repairing the problem in the near future.  I went as far as to tell the GM I would duplicate it for him if he wanted, but he said its not necessary.<br><br>This can be done solo as I am a 54 Druid with 171 wis, just use Form of the Howler and med while he is rooted and dotted.  I was oom when he was 10% health left, so  memmed Creeping Crud to keep him from regenerating HP back while I med and actually found that it took about 3 casts of that spell to drop him.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Beebe Lytcaster 51 Heretic<br>Hiyeedi Fliess 57 Preserver<br>Sarany Richmen 32 Warrior<br>Rallos Zek</td></tr>
