 get lvl 54 back and the person tells me he is giving up on camp and logging.  So I get my ranger friend and we go back.  We call camp check and the broodmother isnt camped so I call her.  We start pulling wurms out and then decide to go in.  We see a monk run past us while running in and sit where the broodmother spawns.  I ask her what shes doing and she says camping broodmother.  I say WTF I got her cmaped and we get in this huge argument.  Anyways she realizes she cant finish the quest alone and leaves BAH.  So we sit down and begin medding.  I get info its going to be 2 hrs till broodmother spawns and decide ill wait it out.  Then all of a sudden this big wurm spawns while medding on top of me.  Im waiting for it to argo on us but doesnt.  WIERD ... so I target it and see Its the broodmother and start shouting woot .   So my group runs to the fort and I give her the harness.  She takes her time to get there(bout 3 mins)  and I follow her.  She gets there and attacks one of the giants.  We run after the other.  I cast root (Resist).  So I think im screwed but it argos on me Yayyyy!!!  So the ranger takes argo off of me and me the other cleric and shaman just root the adds and heal the ranger.  BOOM giant goes down.  I loot legs and im real happy now.  Great legs and the quest I would rate pretty easy if you got patience.<br>-Bagdak lvl 54 cleric on cazic<br>-Thanks for all the help Minian and the other shaman cleric<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
